# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Package version installed: latest available from npm registry
- Dependencies updated in package.json and package-lock.json

### 2. Modified Files

#### front/app/layout.tsx
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the closing `</ThemeProvider>` tag
- Placement ensures analytics tracking is properly initialized for all pages

## Implementation Details

This is an App Router project (Next.js 14.2.3) with the app directory structure. The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (app/layout.tsx) as per Vercel's official documentation for App Router projects.

The component is placed at the end of the body tag to ensure:
- It doesn't interfere with the existing UI structure
- Analytics scripts load after the main content
- Proper tracking across all routes and pages

